  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Laboratory Attendant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description </strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u>Cleaning &amp; Hygiene (Core)</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Clean laboratory benches, sinks, floors and preparation areas. </li>\n  <li>Wash, dry and store glassware, apparatus and other lab tools after use. </li>\n  <li>Safely dispose of laboratory and general waste according to labaratory staff. </li>\n  <li>Maintain cleanliness and orderliness in other Science Research Centre facilities such as lecture theatres, seminar rooms and meeting rooms. </li>\n  <li>Refill cleaning supplies and ensure proper storage of cleaning chemicals. </li>\n  <li>Maintain general tidiness and organisation of storage areas and shared spaces. </li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Support Tasks (Complementary) </u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist in setting up and clearing equipment, apparatus, and materials for lessons, research projects, seminars, events, and workshops.</li>\n  <li>Monitor and replenish laboratory consumables (e.g. gloves, PPE, stationery, common reagents).</li>\n  <li>Assist in basic equipment maintenance checks and report faulty or damaged items.</li>\n  <li>Follow all safety protocols, including correct personal protective equipment usage.</li>\n  <li>Support logistics for departmental events, competitions, and special science activities.</li>\n  <li>Provide basic guidance to students on handling laboratory tools safely during setup or cleaning.</li>\n  <li>Perform other duties as assigned by the laboratory manager or staff.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements </strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Qualification: Secondary education level.</li>\n  <li>Physically fit and able to perform manual cleaning  and lifting tasks.</li>\n  <li>Prior experience in a school or laboratory  environment preferred.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of basic laboratory safety and safe  handling of cleaning chemicals preferred.</li>\n  <li>Comfortably working in Biology, Chemistry, and  Physics laboratory settings.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in basic English.</li>\n  <li>Able to work independently, responsibly, and as part  of a team.</li>\n</ul>",
